    {
      "id": "el_60",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1005,
      "y": 1577,
      "width": 288,
      "height": 231,
      "text": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Father's only daughter = Meena\nStep 2: Son of Meena = the boy\n\n  [+Father]\n      │\n    [-Meena]  <- only daughter\n      │\n    [+Boy]\n\nTRICK:\n\"only daughter of my father\" = myself(F)\nReplace and read: \"son of myself\"\n= my son. So Meena is his Mother.\n\nAnswer: Meena is the boy's Mother ✓",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
